generateDoc

@Nullable
public java.lang.String generateDoc(com.intellij.psi.PsiElement element,
                                             @Nullable
                                             com.intellij.psi.PsiElement originalElement)
Generates the documentation (if available) for element. This does two things, first it looks whether the element is a Symbol. If this is true it tries to load the usage message. If element is not a Symbol, it is possibly an operator. Then it tries to guess the usage message of the operator by converting the class name to a hopefully valid operator name.

Specified by:
generateDoc in interface com.intellij.lang.documentation.DocumentationProvider
Overrides:
generateDoc in class com.intellij.lang.documentation.DocumentationProviderEx
Parameters:
element - Element which was possibly altered by getCustomDocumentationElement(Editor, PsiFile, PsiElement) or by getDocumentationElementForLookupItem(PsiManager, Object, PsiElement) if the lookup was active
originalElement - The original element for which the doc was called (possibly whitespace)
Returns:
The html string of the usage message or null if it could not be loaded

getCustomDocumentationElement

@Nullable
public com.intellij.psi.PsiElement getCustomDocumentationElement(@NotNull
                                                                          com.intellij.openapi.editor.Editor editor,
                                                                          @NotNull
                                                                          com.intellij.psi.PsiFile file,
                                                                          @Nullable
                                                                          com.intellij.psi.PsiElement contextElement)
Calculates the correct element for which the user wants documentation.

Overrides:
getCustomDocumentationElement in class com.intellij.lang.documentation.DocumentationProviderEx
Parameters:
editor - The editor of the file
file - The file which is edited and where the doc call was made
contextElement - The element where the caret was when the doc was called
Returns:
The element for which the user wants documentation. If an item of the completion list is currently highlighted, then this element. If the cursor is over/beside an identifier, then the symbol element. As last thing it is determined whether the PsiElement is the operator-sign of an operation, then we get the corresponding operation psi implementation element back.
